{"id": "fa5uxr", "title": "A Mathematical Proof for Those scared of 3x Bullish Leveraged ETF's", "selftext": "Conjecture: TQQQ only drops to $0 if QQQ drops more than 1/3 in a single trading day.\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nLet X be the share price of TQQQ\n\nLet r be the percentage decrease for a single day of QQQ's share price\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nWe know that r &lt; 1/3 given the conjecture condition\n\nWe know that the percentage decrease for TQQQ will be 3\\*r given the nature of TQQQ\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nif QQQ drops r percent in a day, then\n\n=&gt; TQQQ will drop 3\\*r\n\n=&gt; TQQQ will drop &lt; 3 \\* 1/3\n\n=&gt; TQQQ will drop &lt; 1\n\n=&gt; TQQQ will drop a percentage less than 1 (100%)\n\n=&gt; TQQQ's share price will drop to: X' = X - X \\* y     --where y is less than 1\n\n=&gt; X' = X \\* ( 1 - y )     --again where y is less than 1\n\n=&gt; X' = X \\* ( z )     --where z is greater than 0, because y is less than 1\n\n=&gt; X' &gt; 0\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nThus, we see that by the condition of the conjecture (QQQ dropping less than 1/3 in a single trading day), and by the nature of TQQQ, the share price of TQQQ will be greater than $0.\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nQED", "created_utc": 1582774337, "permalink": "/r/wallstreetbets/comments/fa5uxr/a_mathematical_proof_for_those_scared_of_3x/", "is_self": true}